>Forgotten Places Chapter 5
I had forgot so much that I read the story, that I somehow thought that I've actually read it last year.
Surely the brain demons mentioned in this chapter are to blame.
Starts little dry with the contracts and court proceedings, but I see that it's necessary setup for the later chapters.
They really put a harsh sentence on Sneevi, how is she supposed to recover from that on her own? Live in a trashcan?
I retract my statement, that other Skiv got it way worse!
The agency went from mysterious and kinda cool to pretty evil in this chapter, is that intended?

>Chapter 6
The agency looks even worse than it did in the previous chapter.
Mike and Sneevi finally meet again, too bad they had some rough weeks behind them and they're treating each other rather poorly.
There was a sweet moment too when Mike made the comparison to a kletchree and asked her if she needed a break, maybe we can get more nicer interactions like this in future chapters?
Everything is set up for the real adventure to begin now, I'm sure you already thought of something great with all the other worldbuilding you've already had in your story so far.

>Silver Hound, Black Moon
Another story that's in desperate need of a short blurb when new chapters go up!
I've only made it through the first 6 chapters so far (in one sitting), but the interactions between the guy "Havelock" and the waifur "Sif" have captivated me so far.
It doesn't take long until we get straight to the good stuff, no I'm not talking about smut.
Havelock, a monster hunter, finds Sif wounded, who got into this state thanks to his friend and only colleague.
He was sent to finish the job, but after showing she's sapient he decides to nurse her back to patch her together instead.
The next 5 chapters are about gaining each others trust with some tense and even a pretty cute moment.
Since I want to urge (You) to read this story yourself, that's all I'm going to say for now.
